oblem is that there are still some subtleties to be considered, e.g. the `subtypes` closure uses the related symbol rather than the occurrence directly, leaving us essentially with only the definition lookup, which we could abstract over (also `supertypes` will get some more special logic with https://github.com/apple/sourcekit-lsp/pull/582/files#r916912420). Since we need both the definition and the symbol location, we'd need these values separately anyway. If you feel strongly about this, I could try and see, but I don't think we would gain much from factoring/unifying these methods.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 8, 15, 26, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'fwcd', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916927880, 'comment_body': 'Yes, I meant type hierarchy.

